<br>
what do i mean by that?<br>
<br>
you want to draw clothing so do something like this:<br>
get many pictures of people wearing clothing from magazines or the internet (magazines are better), also, get a shirt or pair of shorts and put it in an odd position on your bed.  then take a sketchbook out and redraw the magazine pictures exactly how you see them, same thing with the clothes on yoru bed.  this will let your hands remember how to draw folds and clothing.  after this, move on and start designing your own clothes. but make shure you do this many times, and whenever you are in a slump come back to doing this. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=jboxer>JBoxer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/17/02 1:07:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3975.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hey, i need some art tips</span><hr size=1> thanks man i never thought of that, good idea. he and i dont exactly get this but every time i draw i draw my pictures smaller size, like manga or something, &amp; if i draw them a little large thaty dont look as good <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/usimonm5.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SimonM5</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/17/02 2:59:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3975.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.boomspeed.com/simon/headshot.jpg width=122 height=125></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: hey, i need some art 